    <h2>
      <a href="/episodes/63-model-name-in-url">Model Name in URL</a>
      
    </h2>
    <div class="description">
      By default, Rails uses the model&#x27;s id in the URL. What if you want to use the name of the model instead? You can change this behavior by overriding the to_param method in the model. Watch this episode for details.
      <span class="stats">(6 minutes)</span>
    </div>
